   Commerce Seal

                United States Department of Commerce

                Office of General Counsel
     __________________________________________________________________

  The General Counsel is the chief legal officer of the U.S. Department of
  Commerce.

    Offices within the Office of General Counsel include:

     * Commercial Law Development Program
     * Assistant General Counsel for Legislation and Regulation
     * Assistant General Counsel for Administration

     * Employment and Labor Law Division
     * Ethics Division
     * General Law Division

     Assistant General Counsel for Finance and Litigation
     * Contract Law Division
     * Commercial Litigation Division
     * Federal Assistance Law Division
     * General Litigation Division
     * Special Matters Division

     General Counsel National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration

     Solicitor Patent and Trademark Office

     Chief Counsel for Economic Development Administration

     Chief Counsel for Economics & Statistics Administration

     Chief Counsel for Export Administration

     Chief Counsel for Import Administration

     Chief Counsel for International Commerce

     Chief Counsel for Minority Business Development Administration

     Chief Counsel for National Telecommunications and Information
   Administration

     Chief Counsel for Technology Administration

